title: For Sale:  Israeli k98
postcontent: K98 Israeli Mauser – The reeiver is a DOU .45 mix of Czech and German parts. Built by Mauser for the German Army in 1945, near the end of WWII. It was accepted by the Germans and stamped with at least 4 Waffenamts. After the war it was sent to Czechoslovakia and had a post war stock put on it (as indicated by the finger grips). Around 1947 it was sold to the Israeli’s and the Star of David was stamped on it. Most German K98’s received by the Israeli’s had the Waffenamts ground off. However, this rifle has at least 4 remaining Waffenamts. She has been through a lot, there pitting in the barrel and all over the rifle. the stock has a lot of dents and cuts but soild no cracks.
